track.name: All The Things You Are
comments: The brilliant saxophonist who became at the origins of modern jazz.

Full of atmosphere. Way ahead of his time and the pioneer of modern jazz.
Beautiful melody and put together by a genius. Thank you Bird of Paradise.

So beautiful, but how could the audience not be entranced and just pay respect and listen, I'm sure their conversation wasn't so important. Pleased to hear a few people did manage a ripple of applause at the end.
i love this recording...everything comes together so smoothly...and bird is at his understated best...
charlie parker is like that pair of sunglasses that goes with every outfit

la penúltima, no pago un duro.
